You're right, the issue is more fundamental. The problem is that the checklist labels in the PDF contain the checkbox HTML markup from the form. Let me provide the fix for the renderForm method where the checklist labels are created, as well as the PDF generation:

Fix 1: In the renderForm method, clean the checkbox labels:

Replace this section in renderForm:

```javascript
const chkLabel = (id, label, val) => `<label>${chk(id, val)} ${label}</label>`;
```

With this:

```javascript
const chkLabel = (id, label, val) => {
    // Clean the label text - remove any HTML or special characters
    const cleanLabel = label.replace(/[✓✗]/g, '').replace(/\s+/g, ' ').trim();
    return `<label>${chk(id, val)} ${cleanLabel}</label>`;
};
```

Fix 2: In the generateReport function, clean the checklist labels properly:

Replace this section in the checklist summary:

```javascript
section.items.forEach(([label, done]) => {
    const status = done ? '✓' : '✗';
    const color = done ? '#10b981' : '#dc2626';
    doc.setTextColor(color);
    // Clean the label text to remove any HTML/checkbox artifacts
    const cleanLabel = label.replace(/✓\s*/g, '').replace(/\s+/g, ' ').trim();
    doc.text(`${status}  ${cleanLabel}`, margin + 4, y);
    y += 5;
});
```

With this:

```javascript
section.items.forEach(([label, done]) => {
    const status = done ? '✓' : '✗';
    const color = done ? '#10b981' : '#dc2626';
    doc.setTextColor(color);
    // Stronger cleaning - remove any non-word characters and normalize spaces
    let cleanLabel = label.replace(/[^\w\s.,!?\-()'"]/g, ' ').replace(/\s+/g, ' ').trim();
    // If label still has strange characters, just use the raw label but remove common HTML
    if (cleanLabel.length < 3 || cleanLabel.includes('&')) {
        cleanLabel = label.replace(/<[^>]*>/g, '').replace(/&[^;]+;/g, '').replace(/\s+/g, ' ').trim();
    }
    doc.text(`${status}  ${cleanLabel}`, margin + 4, y);
    y += 5;
});
```

Fix 3: Also ensure the data being saved has clean labels - in the collectForm method, add:

```javascript
// Add this at the beginning of collectForm:
const cleanLabel = (str) => {
    if (!str) return '';
    return str.replace(/[^\w\s.,!?\-()'"]/g, ' ').replace(/\s+/g, ' ').trim();
};
```

The real issue is that when the form data is saved, the checkbox labels might be storing HTML entities or special characters. The fixes above will clean the text at both the form rendering stage and the PDF generation stage, ensuring the checklist items appear as plain readable text in the PDF report.
